<subSubSection id="40FC5F07B59FA89A53956346D00E2D83" pageId="null" pageNumber="472" type="description">
<paragraph id="FCF604AC8CD6DC0D159FC73C4B4535AD" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">
Unterscheidet sich von unsern Arten der Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="A15ED06B868790087DB265C64ACD87B1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Crataegus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="null" pageNumber="472" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9B53D7F77E7F1BD8B94C3FCF5BFECA8C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">Crataegus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(S. 470) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="1815AD94676E1B483261A3400D0025C6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">
<normalizedToken id="327A62BC749D727805D0A05118C0B813" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="BFDD08DA450F633988DC29ECD723F22D" originalValue="immergrün" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">immergruen</normalizedToken>
, lanzettlich oder oval, 
<normalizedToken id="E76631A7CE1133678D339AE3551D9A7C" originalValue="gezähnt" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">gezaehnt</normalizedToken>
; Griffel 5.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="61DDC31EC8719FFBBA4E100391887E65" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">
Die Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="1B764D18D0D45CB4A22945355CCBDE45" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Pyracantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="null" pageNumber="472" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F436F0FB40E82C9B2EB56A4542AC7175" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">Pyracantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="86E1D61F0466B3CAA46BB1FFB6FC77E3" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">umfasst</normalizedToken>
etwa 
<emphasis id="319A17C8522AFF32BDF334AA76D2AF18" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">10 Arten in Eurasien</emphasis>
, die meist in den Gattungen 
<taxonomicName id="169E13D73ECBE33F53C21D25B19128B4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="null" pageNumber="472" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6EC70390937ABE9F9A15FE2C15FEF0B8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">Cotoneaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
oder 
<taxonomicName id="52BCD226311FE29D3EC79B7451102A37" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Crataegus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="null" pageNumber="472" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12FE36DC8CE6DEAE97CC68BFE53EC928" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">Crataegus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
untergebracht werden. Da die von uns aufgenommene Art in wesentlichen Merkmalen von unsern Arten der Gattungen 
<taxonomicName id="523532E780C2313CA25C7F088282588C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="null" pageNumber="472" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="586E3572BF986BD2CA1DCE67304C4C1F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">Cotoneaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<taxonomicName id="8130526CBA0EAD184ECDE159AC1A3532" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Crataegus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="null" pageNumber="472" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="39902AECA63A6F60A6409C78587CD280" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="472">Crataegus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
abweicht, ziehen wir es vor, sie in einer besondern Gattung einzureihen.
</paragraph>
